    • Method Detail

      • onMoveBegin

        boolean onMoveBegin(MoveGestureDetector detector)
        Indicates that the move gesture started.
        Parameters:
        detector - this detector
        Returns:
        true if you want to receive subsequent onMove(MoveGestureDetector, float, float) callbacks, false if you want to ignore this gesture.

      • onMove

        boolean onMove(MoveGestureDetector detector,
               float distanceX,
               float distanceY)
        Called for every move change during the gesture.
        Parameters:
        detector - this detector
        distanceX - X distance of the focal point in pixel since last call
        distanceY - Y distance of the focal point in pixel since last call
        Returns:
        true if the gesture was handled, false otherwise

      • onMoveEnd

        void onMoveEnd(MoveGestureDetector detector,
               float velocityX,
               float velocityY)
        Indicates that the move gesture ended.
        Parameters:
        velocityX - velocityX of the gesture in the moment of lifting the fingers
        velocityY - velocityY of the gesture in the moment of lifting the fingers
        detector - this detector
